    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite the overall COU2 regulatory decision being 'Not accepted' due to multiple credibility factor gaps at MRL 5, the credibility assessment package itself is accepted as a complete and valid characterization of the current state of evidence. Seven of thirteen factors were assessed; six remain as documented epistemic gaps. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed for primary model inputs and is discussed throughout the assessment narrative. Aleatory variability from blood donor differences and measurement scatter is acknowledged in prose across several validation result descriptions; however, not all validation result entries carry a formal linked UQ artifact — the hemolysis speed-sensitivity and pressure-head curve results lack explicit UQ node references because those sub-studies were completed under a separate contract deliverable not yet reconciled with this package. The assessment team accepts the package as the authoritative credibility record pending UQ artifact ingestion in the next revision cycle.",
